ia.com/psx/bof4/art13/drag-11.jpg height=80width=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Spare a change (of ideas)?</span><hr size=1> I've got an art exhibition coming up and the deadline is three days away.... The thing is I don't want to show off or anything, I just want to exhibit something -anime to be presice- to (as someone put it) market myself for future carrers involving animation... Which is why I need to do some artwork with characters in dynamic poses (you don't expect artwork of people standing or sitting around would impress people much...) <br>
*takes a deep breath*<br>
So can anyone recommend a place for such stuff (as in getting refrence for dynamic poses)...?<br>
Also I'm willing to hear suggestions or ideas if you have any... <br>
(BTW I tried the Poses forum, but didn't find what I had in mind...)<br>
I thank you all in advance <br>
<br>
[edit] should I post some a couple of fanarts (with credits given and refrences mentioned?) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uashjaded.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ash Jaded </A> at: 4/17/01 6:42:28 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uevnhnssn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>evn hnssn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/17/01 9:25:34 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www16.brinkster.com/evnhnssn/evnezp.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spare a change (of ideas)?</span><hr size=1> (sorry for a long response!)<br>
<br>
as a vague, distant memory i recall one of Sensei Patrick's tutorials defining a 'line of direction' or 'flow' which makes a pose dynamic. that is, with a stick figure pose. it can be the spine... or the arm... anything. i also recall a couple of examples that displayed particular gestures or actions.<br>
<br>
you can check there -or- as a suggestion, try poses in a mirror. it works for me (but that is probably because i do lots of dancing, so poses come easy).<br>
<br>
if you have enough time, i recommend trying to 'create' three frames- some quick &quot;basic object exercise&quot; happening. &quot;basic object exercise&quot; refers to (in drama) an object in use by an actor that would keep the attention of the audience... for example, spilling a cup of coffee -or- jump-roping -or- combing hair -or- looking at watch, etc.<br>
<br>
as to references to dynamic poses (besides Sensei's), i regret to inform you that i have none.<br>
<br>
.evn. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uspikescafe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SpikesCafe</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.spikescafe.com/shell.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/17/01 9:58:35 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.spikescafe.com/crit/torticon.gif height=100 width=127></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spare a change (of ideas)?</span><hr size=1> Besides just perspective, which I did somewhat mediocrely <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.spikescafe.com/crit/gabby2.jpg">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, I've found that a twisting at the hips also makes your character look much more dynamic. Also, if you're having trouble finding a dynamic pose to model a drawing after, I'd suggest doing a little &quot;thumbnail&quot; sketch where you make a stick figure, possibly flesh it in a little, and decide from there. I also seem to remember there's a How To Draw Manga book that covers, in depth, how to make your drawings more dynamic. Seeing as how you don't have much time, though, that probably won't help. Sorry I can't do more! <p>-<a href="http://www.spikescafe.com/gallery/main.html">Spike the Tortoise</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uashjaded.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ash Jaded </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/17/01 10:39:15 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thegia.com/psx/bof4/art13/drag-11.jpg height=80width=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spare a change (of ideas)?</span><hr size=1> Great, great...<br>
thank you both for your helpful tips... esp. the 'hip twist' tip... I guess that's something I overlooked but it has a great effect... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udarkora.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/18/01 2:16:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spare a change (of ideas)?</span><hr size=1> A little late here (and a little new to the forum), but I thought I'd throw out a suggestion that helps me out.  When practicing dynamic stuff, I'll take something that I view as an incredible move or action sequence from a movie and try to recreate it.  As I'm doing so, I'll purposely over-exaggerate the pose and try to switch to a different viewing angle/perspective to see what kind of effect this has on the &quot;feel&quot; of the drawing.  Anyways, it seems to work for me (but then again, I'm not that good...yet).   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uashjaded.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ash Jaded </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/19/01 8:24:42 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thegia.com/psx/bof4/art13/drag-11.jpg height=80width=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spare a change (of ideas)?</span><hr size=1> hmmm... thought of thid but never tried it... (I'm too slow to catch action)<br>
